          <name>Introduced in House</name>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Helping Our Middle-Class Entrepreneurs Act or the HOME Act</strong> </p> <p> This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow a taxpayer who uses a residence to conduct a trade or business a standard tax deduction equal to the lesser of $1,500 or the taxpayer's gross trade or business income derived from the business use of such residence. The bill provides for an inflation adjustment to the standard deduction amount in calendar years beginning after 2017.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2017-02-02T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
